- add a visible <h1> with a unique id at the top of the dialog to introduce the content, then reference it placing aria-labelledby on to the wrapper, pointing to the heading's ID
- role="dialog" tells screen reader users that this is a dialog, which helps set their expectations going forward.
- aria-modal="true" causes screen readers to automatically trap their users' virtual cursor inside this element, similar to the keyboard focus trap that we have to implement manually. This attribute is specifically for screen reader users, and the focus trap is for keyboard-only users.
